[{"question":"Put him in context, historical context, how important was Dick Clark, do you think?","answer":"Well, he was a pioneer, in the -- you know, in the early days of television, with \"American Bandstand,\" he revolutionized music on television.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":38,"aSentId":39},{"question":"Isn\u0027t that amazing?","answer":"Amazing.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":53,"aSentId":54},{"question":"What was the secret ingredient that he had?","answer":"He was a great generalist.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":63,"aSentId":64},{"question":"What was Dick\u0027s importance to you, your career and your life?","answer":"Well, there would have been no career without Dick Clark.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":82,"aSentId":83},{"question":"Do you think in the end that he realized that wasn\u0027t what was important to his life?","answer":"RANCIS: Well, it was really up until -- I think I saw him a year and a half ago, I went to visit Kari and Dick in Malibu, their home.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":94,"aSentId":95},{"question":"What was the importance of \"American Bandstand\" to any young musical act in America?","answer":"It was the show that everybody wanted to be on because it presented their talent.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":111,"aSentId":112},{"question":"How many people -- of all the people that you ever interviewed had that distinctive, gut feel for what the majority of Americans would love to see or hear?","answer":"I have to think of it -- Steve Jobs, interviewed him early on, he had it.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":193,"aSentId":194},{"question":"Was that your experience?","answer":"Actually, Piers, I got an experience that \"Donny and Marie Show.\"","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":226,"aSentId":227},{"question":"What did he do, how was he in that persuasive mode?","answer":"Well, I got to tell you, I think only Dick Clark could have talked me into doing that, because, you know, twice in my life my knees have knocked, and that was one of them.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":248,"aSentId":249},{"question":"What was it about him that enabled him to persuade people they had the confidence to do stuff?","answer":"He was an every man.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":302,"aSentId":303},{"question":"What do you think America has lost today?","answer":"They have lost an institution, when these -- when these people leave us, they leave a hole that doesn\u0027t get filled.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":315,"aSentId":316},{"question":"How big a moment is that for any musical act?","answer":"Think I appreciate it now more than I did then, because back then, we were still very much kids.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":348,"aSentId":349},{"question":"William, he says it all there, Lionel, doesn\u0027t it?","answer":"You know, the thing is that I remember one time we first met, he kept saying gentlemen, gentlemen to us, because -- say that to us.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":375,"aSentId":376},{"question":"And did you realize at the time what a big deal it was?","answer":"You know, I did realize.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":406,"aSentId":407},{"question":"Is it a stretch to say that Dick Clark played a really significant and valuable role in the civil rights movement because of the way that he brought black performers and black bands and music to mainstream American television?","answer":"I don\u0027t think it\u0027s a stretch at all.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":439,"aSentId":440},{"question":"What was it about him, do you think, that made him so universally popular?","answer":"I think it is what the guys were saying, that he didn\u0027t put his own opinion -- he really represented the music that America loved and wanted to hear.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":463,"aSentId":464},{"question":"He was really, as Larry King and others said earlier, pretty unique and pretty irreplaceable, wasn\u0027t he?","answer":"He was sprinkling, you know, this magical dust of sorts across television with award shows and reality shows and game shows.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":506,"aSentId":507},{"question":"Would you go along with that?","answer":"I think a lot of people in the television industry do feel like he\u0027s the closest.","docId":"120418pmt","qSentId":518,"aSentId":519}]